&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT THE ROLE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Senior Enterprise Project Manager&lt;/strong&gt; owns the business casing, planning, delivery, adoption, and governance of strategic projects that sit at the intersection of technology and business. This role is the connective tissue between stakeholders who define the vision and the teams who build and deliver, responsible for end-to-end execution across technical and non-technical workstreams.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;A defining characteristic of this role is the ability to bridge technology and business: translating complex data and systems initiatives into structured delivery plans with clear accountability, timelines, and outcomes. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT YOU&#39;LL WORK ON&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
