&lt;li&gt;Structure ambiguous, complex business problems into clear analytical frameworks and workplans.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build financial models and conduct quantitative analysis to diagnose business issues, size market opportunities, and assess the costs, benefits, and trade-offs of strategic options.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Synthesize complex, often conflicting information into crisp narratives and compelling recommendations tailored for executive and Board-level audiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive projects through to implementation, maintaining accountability for outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Planning, Performance Reporting &amp;amp; Market Intelligence&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the annual strategic planning process at the business unit and portfolio level.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct competitive benchmarking, market sizing, and industry research; translate findings into clear implications and recommendations for the business.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor trends across the luxury travel landscape and surface insights that sharpen Kensington’s strategic positioning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the preparation of materials for leadership offsites, Board presentations, and strategic reviews.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain KPIs, scorecards, and reporting frameworks that enable data-driven decision-making across the organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
